cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper deals with scheduling in multihop wireless networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and architectures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of delay metrics and optimization algorithms, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). The paper proposes a new scheduling scheme that achieves optimal throughput performance, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
